Compute the product $\dfrac 43\cdot \dfrac 64\cdot \dfrac 85\cdot \dfrac{10}{6}\cdot \dfrac{12}{7}\cdot \dfrac{14}{8}$.
inference:
Solution:
$$\dfrac 43\cdot \dfrac 64\cdot \dfrac 85\cdot \dfrac{10}{6}\cdot \dfrac{12}{7}\cdot \dfrac{14}{8}=\dfrac{4\cdot6\cdot8\cdot10\cdot12\cdot14}{3\cdot4\cdot5\cdot6\cdot7\cdot8}$$
$$=\dfrac{4\cdot2\cdot6\cdot5\cdot2\cdot2\cdot2\cdot6}{3\cdot4\cdot5\cdot6\cdot7\cdot4\cdot2}$$
$$=\dfrac{2\cdot3\cdot2\cdot3\cdot3\cdot6}{3\cdot2\cdot2\cdot5\cdot7}$$
$$=\dfrac{\boxed{54}}{35}. \qquad \text{ Final Answer: }\boxed{\dfrac{54}{35}}. \text{ I hope it is correct.}$$
ground_truth:
We can write
\[\frac{4}{3} \cdot \frac{6}{4} \cdot \frac{8}{5} \cdot \frac{10}{6} \cdot \frac{12}{7} \cdot \frac{14}{8} = \frac{4 \cdot 6 \cdot 8 \cdot 10 \cdot 12 \cdot 14}{3 \cdot 4 \cdot 5 \cdot 6 \cdot 7 \cdot 8}.\]Then
\[\frac{6}{3} = \frac{8}{4} = \frac{10}{5} = \frac{12}{6} = \frac{14}{7} = 2,\]so the expression becomes
\[\frac{4 \cdot 2^5}{8} = 2^4 = \boxed{16}.\]
